{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"30b8ff31-1652-4932-820d-8b97d5330fb8","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then:**\n- Install the .NET 11 SDK locally (`dotnet --version` to confirm).\n- Run `dotnet restore` to pull updated packages.\n- Check for breaking changes in the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/) and update any NuGet packages (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`) to their 11.x versions.\n- Build and test: `dotnet build && dotnet test`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8b6cb95d-cbd9-4435-b431-ce7c6063c94c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to update their .NET 10 ASP.NET Core web app to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to search their codebase since they've described the files.","outputTokens":331,"requestId":"9838:B7F6F:2AAED3:353FDE:69F5562F"},"id":"2e01af8f-8f11-47b9-8475-46adad6ffa67","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:41:11.127Z","parentId":"cc5666c4-6d0c-4f85-a4c8-c9385b793d14"}
